Alternatively, we can use the `List.foldr` definition directly:

`foldr1 f xs = List.foldr f (List.getLast xs) xs` where `List.getLast` gives the last element of the list. But this requires `xs ≠ []`.

So, for `foldr1 f (xs ++ ys)`:
