- So, `foldr1 f (xs ++ ys) = List.foldr f (List.getLast ys) (xs ++ ys)`

And `f (foldr1 f xs) (foldr1 f ys)`:
- `foldr1 f xs = List.foldr f (List.getLast xs) xs` (since `xs ≠ []`)
- `foldr1 f ys = List.foldr f (List.getLast ys) ys` (since `ys ≠ []`)
- So, `f (foldr1 f xs) (foldr1 f ys) = f (List.foldr f (List.getLast xs) xs) (List.foldr f (List.getLast ys) ys)`

Now, we need to prove:
`List.foldr f (List.getLast ys) (xs ++ ys) = f (List.foldr f (List.getLast xs) xs) (List.foldr f (List.getLast ys) ys)`

This can be approached by using properties of `List.foldr` and concatenation. 

Alternatively, we can use the `List.foldr` definition directly and prove it by induction.

